      "status": "shipped",
      "description": "Operator created 'Taylor Grift' agent (likely from the Agents tab or Chat tab) and it didn't appear in the Canvas Conversations palette — the palette only loaded its agents list once at canvas-page construction. Fixed by overriding CanvasPage.showEvent to call palette.reload_agents() every time the operator navigates to the Canvas tab. Cheap (single agents.list RPC); fires only on tab switch. Also shipped a multi-select Skills picker (per the operator's request 'set skills for the agent per model and select them'): new skills.list RPC scans ~/.claude/skills/ for Claude; new SkillsPicker dialog wired to a 'Browse skills…' button on Chat tab + Canvas New-Conversation dialog.",
      "change_overview": [
        "apps/gui/canvas/page.py — CanvasPage.showEvent overrides Qt's default to fire palette.reload_agents() on every tab visit",
        "apps/service/main.py — new skills_list RPC scanning ~/.claude/skills/*.md; description picked from front-matter description: or first non-empty body line",
